  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large cazuela over medium heat.",
    "Sauté diced onion until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Mince garlic and sauté for another minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add jamaican seasoning blend, ground ginger, cumin, salt, and black pepper. Stir for 1 minute.",
    "Add chickpea flour and stir for 2 minutes, until well combined with spices.",
    "Add chicken broth and coconut milk, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.",
    "Bring mixture to a simmer and cook for 20 minutes, until thickened and heated through.",
    "Remove from heat and stir in chopped scotch bonnet peppers.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs, if desired.",
    "Let stew rest for 10 minutes before serving to allow flavors to meld."
  ],
